{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit15SnapshotManagerO","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnapshotManager","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"enum","title":"SnapshotManager","roleHeading":"Enumeration","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SnapshotManager"},{"text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the VM’s disk image (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"text":") and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"auxiliary.bin"},{"text":"), stored in a named subdirectory under the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SavedStates\/"},{"text":" directory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How Snapshots Work","level":2,"anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"must be stopped","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" before saving or restoring.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the snapshot copies.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Snapshot Directory Layout","level":2,"anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout","type":"heading"},{"code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"text":"Example","level":2,"anchor":"Example","type":"heading"},{"code":["let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","","\/\/ Save a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.save(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ List snapshots","let snapshots = try SnapshotManager.list(bundle: bundle)","for snap in snapshots {","    print(\"\\(snap.label): \\(snap.sizeInBytes) bytes\")","}","","\/\/ Restore a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.restore(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ Delete a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.delete(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\